==English==

===Etymology===
Recorded since 1656; from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|lang=grc|εὐφημισμός|tr=euphēmismos}} < {{term|lang=grc|εὐφημίζω|tr=euphēmizō}} < {{term|lang=grc|εὔφημος|tr=euphēmos||uttering sound of good omen, abstaining from inauspicious words}} < {{term|εὖ|sc=polytonic|tr=eu||well}} + {{term|lang=grc|φήμη|tr=phēmē||a voice, a prophetic voice, rumor, talk}} < {{term|lang=grc|φάναι|tr=phanai||to speak, say}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|yoo͞'fə-mĭz"(ə)m}}, {{IPA|/ˈjuː.fəˌmɪ.z(ə)m/}}, {{SAMPA|/"ju:f@%mIz(@)m/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{uncountable}} The use of a word or phrase to replace another with one that is considered less [[offensive]] or less [[vulgar]] than the word or phrase it replaces.
# {{countable}} {{figure of speech}} A word or phrase that is used to replace another in this way.

